### Shipment Compliance Automation — example requests
###
### Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension (or JetBrains HTTP client):
### open this file and click "Send Request" above each block, top to bottom.
### The blocks share variables, so run them in order. curl equivalents are in the README.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 1. Create the sample shipment (from the assignment)
# @name create
POST {{baseUrl}}/shipments
Content-Type: application/json
x-actor: ops-analyst

{
  "shipment_reference": "SAF-IMP-2026-0007",
  "exporter": "BlueRiver Manufacturing Ltd",
  "importer": "Eastland Retail Group",
  "invoice_number": "INV-77821",
  "invoice_value": 48250.0,
  "currency": "USD",
  "goods_description": "Industrial water pumps and spare impellers",
  "hs_code": "8413.70",
  "country_of_origin": "CN",
  "gross_weight_kg": 12750,
  "net_weight_kg": 12100,
  "number_of_packages": 42,
  "container_number": "MSCU1234567",
  "bill_of_lading": "BL-SHA-7788",
  "packaging_type": "wooden crates",
  "ispm15_certified": null,
  "arrival_date": "2026-06-20"
}

@shipmentId = {{create.response.body.id}}

### 2. Ingest a mock document (a partner feed that disagrees on the invoice value)
POST {{baseUrl}}/shipments/{{shipmentId}}/documents
Content-Type: application/json
x-actor: ops-analyst

{
  "source": "partner_feed",
  "payload": {
    "shipment_reference": "SAF-IMP-2026-0007",
    "invoice_value": 50000.0,
    "hs_code": "8413.70"
  }
}

### 3. Run the compliance validation engine
POST {{baseUrl}}/shipments/{{shipmentId}}/validate
x-actor: ops-analyst

### 4. Fetch the issues from the latest run
GET {{baseUrl}}/shipments/{{shipmentId}}/issues

### 5. Generate the readiness report
GET {{baseUrl}}/shipments/{{shipmentId}}/readiness-report

### 6. Read the full audit trail
GET {{baseUrl}}/shipments/{{shipmentId}}/audit-log

### 7. Attempt to approve a blocked shipment (expected: 409 INVALID_STATE)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/shipments/{{shipmentId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
x-actor: reviewer-1

{ "status": "approved" }

### 8. Fetch one shipment (with document count + latest validation summary)
GET {{baseUrl}}/shipments/{{shipmentId}}

### 9. List all shipments
GET {{baseUrl}}/shipments

### --- A "clean" shipment that passes and can be approved ---

### 10. Create a fully valid shipment
# @name createClean
POST {{baseUrl}}/shipments
Content-Type: application/json
x-actor: ops-analyst

{
  "shipment_reference": "SAF-IMP-2026-0009",
  "exporter": "BlueRiver Manufacturing Ltd",
  "importer": "Eastland Retail Group",
  "invoice_number": "INV-77822",
  "invoice_value": 48250.0,
  "currency": "USD",
  "goods_description": "Industrial water pumps and spare impellers",
  "hs_code": "8413.70",
  "country_of_origin": "CN",
  "gross_weight_kg": 12750,
  "net_weight_kg": 12100,
  "number_of_packages": 42,
  "container_number": "CSQU3054383",
  "bill_of_lading": "BL-SHA-7799",
  "packaging_type": "wooden crates",
  "ispm15_certified": true,
  "arrival_date": "2026-07-01"
}

@cleanId = {{createClean.response.body.id}}

### 11. Validate it (expected: status "ready", 0 issues — assuming a recent arrival date)
POST {{baseUrl}}/shipments/{{cleanId}}/validate
x-actor: ops-analyst

### 12. Approve it (expected: 200, status "approved")
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/shipments/{{cleanId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
x-actor: reviewer-1

{ "status": "approved" }
